text: The comments about rap music and how it was inappropriate lead me to believe that the history behind rap and why it surfaced or has been hijacked by cultural appropriation is not known to those who make that comment. ¬†Rap has long been the background music of black men in strong male-centric roles of film......and people of all walks of life are drawn in and watch for a reason. ¬†Original Gangster with Denzel Washington, Creed with Michael B. Jordan.......I could go on and on. ¬†The point is that rap has been the vehicle of the story of the black struggle. ¬†It is quite fitting for this movie and it is also a genius way to pull young people in to watch and learn about their history.
